---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HeroText from '~/components/widgets/HeroText.astro';

const metadata = { title: 'Terms and Conditions | SSS Health Solutions' };
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <HeroText title="Terms and Conditions" />
  <section class="px-4 py-16 mx-auto max-w-4xl lg:py-20">
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none dark:prose-invert dark:text-slate-400">
      <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 2026</p>
      
      <h3>1. Agreement to Terms</h3>
      <p>By accessing or using the SSS Health Solutions LLC website, you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions.</p>
      
      <h3>2. Independent Advisory Services</h3>
      <p>SSS Health Solutions LLC operates as an independent insurance agency. We provide advisory services and facilitate the application process for health insurance policies. <strong>We do not underwrite insurance policies, and final decisions regarding coverage approval and premium rates are made solely by the insurance carriers.</strong></p>
      
      <h3>3. No Medical Advice</h3>
      <p>The content provided on this website is for informational purposes only. We are licensed insurance brokers, not medical professionals. Nothing stated on this site should be construed as medical advice.</p>
      
      <h3>4. Quotes and Estimates</h3>
      <p>Any premiums or quotes provided are estimates based on the information provided and current carrier pricing. Final rates are subject to the carrier's underwriting process.</p>
      
      <h3>5. Communication Consent (TCPA)</h3>
      <p>By submitting your contact information, you consent to receive communications from SSS Health Solutions LLC regarding your insurance inquiry via phone call, email, and SMS text message. Consent is not a condition of purchase.</p>
      
      <h3>6. Limitation of Liability</h3>
      <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, SSS Health Solutions LLC shall not be liable for any damages resulting from your use of our website, or from the denial of claims or policy cancellations enacted by third-party insurance carriers.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
